{{fbdoc item="title" value="CONDWAIT"}}
----
Stops execution of current thread until some other thread signals that execution can continue.

{{fbdoc item="syntax"}}##
	[[KeyPgDeclare declare]] [[KeyPgSub sub]] **Condwait** ( [[KeyPgByval byval]] //handle// [[KeyPgAs as]] [[KeyPgInteger integer]] )
##
{{fbdoc item="usage"}}##
	**Condwait** ( //handle// )
##
{{fbdoc item="param"}}
	##//handle//##
		The ##[[KeyPgInteger integer]]## handle returned by a previous call to ##[[KeyPgCondCreate Condcreate]]##.

{{fbdoc item="desc"}}
	Function that stops the thread where it is called until some other thread  ##[[KeyPgCondSignal Condsignal]]##s or ##[[KeyPgCondBroadcast Condbroadcast]]##s  the handle.

	Once the conditional is ##[[KeyPgCondCreate Condcreate]]## and the threads are started, one of more of them can be set to ##[[KeyPgCondWait Condwait]]## for the conditional, they will be stopped until some other thread ##[[KeyPgCondSignal Condsignal]]##s that the waiting thread can restart. ##[[KeyPgCondBroadcast Condbroadcast]]## can be used to restart all threads waiting for the conditional. At the end of the program ##[[KeyPgCondDestroy Conddestroy]]## must be used to avoid leaking resources in the OS.

	Multihtreading is not implemented as a service in MSDOS so this fuction does'nt exist in FB for DOS32.

{{fbdoc item="ex"}}
	See ##[[KeyPgCondCreate Condcreate]]##

{{fbdoc item="diff"}}
	- New to FreeBasic

